WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-CA

00:00:01.501 --> 00:00:03.402
&gt;&gt; David: Fasten
your seatbelts.

00:00:03.402 --> 00:00:06.006
Is your car dealership
ripping you off?

00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:08.207
&gt;&gt; 1,200-dollar service
they were recommending.

00:00:08.207 --> 00:00:09.942
None of which was needed.

00:00:09.942 --> 00:00:11.710
&gt;&gt; David: We're undercover.

00:00:11.710 --> 00:00:12.811
&gt;&gt; You guys are
missing everything.

00:00:12.811 --> 00:00:14.747
Tire rotation, brake inspection.

00:00:14.747 --> 00:00:16.315
&gt;&gt; Again, overselling.

00:00:16.315 --> 00:00:17.884
&gt;&gt; David: High-pressure tactics.

00:00:17.884 --> 00:00:19.251
&gt;&gt; I felt like he was
trying to scare me.

00:00:19.251 --> 00:00:21.487
&gt;&gt; David: Plus, insider secrets.

00:00:21.487 --> 00:00:23.189
&gt;&gt; You have to up-sell them.

00:00:23.189 --> 00:00:25.958 align:start position:0%
They come in for an oil change,
you're up-selling somebody.

00:00:25.958 --> 00:00:27.727 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: I'm just trying to get
to the bottom of why you're

00:00:27.727 --> 00:00:30.663
recommending service that
isn't required on a vehicle.

00:00:30.663 --> 00:00:32.665
&gt;&gt; David: This is
your Marketplace.

00:00:32.665 --> 00:00:34.567
[ ♪♪ ]

00:00:35.601 --> 00:00:37.771
&gt;&gt; David: At some point,
we all do this.

00:00:37.771 --> 00:00:40.272
&gt;&gt; Hi, I want to
drop my car off.

00:00:40.272 --> 00:00:41.540
&gt;&gt; David: But when
you bring your car

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:42.976
to the dealership for service...

00:00:45.911 --> 00:00:47.447
&gt;&gt; David: How do you know
what they recommend...

00:00:51.484 --> 00:00:53.886
&gt;&gt; David: ..is what's
really needed?

00:00:53.886 --> 00:00:57.223
[ ♪♪ ]

00:00:57.223 --> 00:01:00.392
&gt;&gt; David: To find out we're
recruiting Jessica Celsie.

00:01:00.392 --> 00:01:02.361
&gt;&gt; You don't really know
who to trust when it comes to

00:01:02.361 --> 00:01:03.829
getting your car fixed.

00:01:03.829 --> 00:01:07.333
&gt;&gt; David: With her newly
purchased 2008 Honda Civic.

00:01:07.333 --> 00:01:09.368
[ ♪♪ ]

00:01:09.368 --> 00:01:10.804
&gt;&gt; David: This is our bait car.

00:01:12.605 --> 00:01:15.975
First, we ask Jessica
to bring it to this garage

00:01:15.975 --> 00:01:18.912 align:start position:0%
for a pre-inspection by licensed
mechanic Mark Whinton.

00:01:20.513 --> 00:01:22.514
&gt;&gt; Hi nice to meet you.
&gt;&gt; Nice to meet you.

00:01:22.514 --> 00:01:24.083
Have you had any
issues with it at all?

00:01:24.083 --> 00:01:25.217
Is there any lights coming on?

00:01:25.217 --> 00:01:26.453
&gt;&gt; Nope, nothing.

00:01:26.453 --> 00:01:27.453
&gt;&gt; Any rattles?

00:01:27.453 --> 00:01:28.454
&gt;&gt; Nope, no rattles.

00:01:28.454 --> 00:01:29.521
&gt;&gt; None whatsoever?

00:01:29.521 --> 00:01:30.656
So it's completely dependable?

00:01:30.656 --> 00:01:32.024
It's starting?
It's running all right?

00:01:32.024 --> 00:01:33.025
&gt;&gt; Yes.

00:01:33.025 --> 00:01:34.093
[ ♪♪ ]

00:01:34.093 --> 00:01:36.362 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: After taking
it for a test drive, he begins.

00:01:40.833 --> 00:01:44.370
Once an instructor, Whinton is
now a vehicle safety advocate.

00:01:46.739 --> 00:01:47.940
The verdict?

00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.977
&gt;&gt; Change the wiper blades,
rotate the tires.

00:01:50.977 --> 00:01:53.078
Ummm, that should be it.

00:01:53.078 --> 00:01:55.848
[ ♪♪ ]

00:01:55.848 --> 00:01:57.851
&gt;&gt; David: Jessica's ready
to check out what this

00:01:57.851 --> 00:02:00.086
Toronto Honda
dealership recommends.

00:02:01.821 --> 00:02:04.257
&gt;&gt; Well, based on my past
experience with dealerships,

00:02:04.257 --> 00:02:06.025
ummm, you know,
i have a feeling

00:02:06.025 --> 00:02:08.294
they're going to
try and up-sell me.

00:02:08.294 --> 00:02:10.462
&gt;&gt; David: And Jessica's
not alone.

00:02:10.462 --> 00:02:13.833
We're hearing similar concerns
about up-selling at dealerships

00:02:13.833 --> 00:02:15.367
from across the country.

00:02:15.367 --> 00:02:17.270
[ ♪♪ ]

00:02:18.637 --> 00:02:21.273
&gt;&gt; David: Including
from Cathy Knight...

00:02:21.273 --> 00:02:22.942
&gt;&gt; This looks like the
road our house is on.

00:02:22.942 --> 00:02:23.943
It would be there but--

00:02:23.943 --> 00:02:26.011
&gt;&gt; No, that's the
way to the park.

00:02:26.011 --> 00:02:29.115 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: Cathy likes to take
her grandson, Joe, around Ottawa

00:02:29.115 --> 00:02:31.684
in her 2011 Ford Fusion.

00:02:31.684 --> 00:02:33.252
&gt;&gt; There's the park.
See, Joe?

00:02:33.252 --> 00:02:34.620
We just passed it.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:36.422
&gt;&gt; David: When her car
needs to be serviced,

00:02:36.422 --> 00:02:39.425
she and her husband Craig always
take it back to the dealership.

00:02:41.293 --> 00:02:43.529
&gt;&gt; David: Why is it important
for you to go to the dealership

00:02:43.529 --> 00:02:45.264
to do your maintenance?

00:02:45.264 --> 00:02:48.234
&gt;&gt; They know the car best, and
i just have confidence in them.

00:02:48.234 --> 00:02:50.403
&gt;&gt; You develop a relationship,
you depend on them to give you

00:02:50.403 --> 00:02:53.840
advice, when they give
you advice, you take it.

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:56.709
&gt;&gt; David: Last fall, Cathy
needed her snow tires put on.

00:02:56.709 --> 00:03:00.446
So Craig makes an appointment
online with their dealership.

00:03:00.446 --> 00:03:03.483
But get this, before
even inspecting her car,

00:03:03.483 --> 00:03:06.785
he gets an email back,
telling him it's also due for

00:03:06.785 --> 00:03:09.521
factory required maintenance.

00:03:09.521 --> 00:03:12.458 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; And it was changing the spark
plugs and the intake manifold

00:03:12.458 --> 00:03:15.128
gasket and changing
the transmission fluid,

00:03:15.128 --> 00:03:16.328
the PCV valve.

00:03:16.328 --> 00:03:18.598
And holy cow,
$1200 bucks worth of stuff?

00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:22.035
i was just going to get the snow
tires put on and an oil change.

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:24.337
&gt;&gt; David: Time to
get a second opinion.

00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:27.306
&gt;&gt; Cars today,
absolutely, unequivocally,

00:03:27.306 --> 00:03:28.507
require less service.

00:03:28.507 --> 00:03:31.543
&gt;&gt; David: So, how do i know,
when i go to the dealership,

00:03:31.543 --> 00:03:32.779
what maintenance i really need?

00:03:32.779 --> 00:03:33.780
&gt;&gt; Oh, that's easy.

00:03:37.517 --> 00:03:40.786
You go to your car.
&gt;&gt; David: Yup.

00:03:40.786 --> 00:03:41.954
Pull out your owner's manual.

00:03:41.954 --> 00:03:45.290
&gt;&gt; You take out the owner's
manual and right here is the

00:03:45.290 --> 00:03:46.792
required maintenance schedule.

00:03:46.792 --> 00:03:51.030
In it will be exactly
what needs to be changed,

00:03:51.030 --> 00:03:52.932
what exactly needs
to be inspected.

00:03:52.932 --> 00:03:56.236
These people
designed and built the car.

00:03:56.236 --> 00:03:59.539
They are the source of
information when it comes to

00:03:59.539 --> 00:04:00.773
maintaining the car.

00:04:00.773 --> 00:04:04.243 line:83%
&gt;&gt; David: What the manufacturer
suggests in the owner's manual

00:04:04.243 --> 00:04:06.312 line:83%
for maintenance and
what the dealer suggests

00:04:06.312 --> 00:04:07.646 line:85%
are two different things?

00:04:07.646 --> 00:04:09.949 line:83%
&gt;&gt; In most cases,
yes that's true.

00:04:09.949 --> 00:04:12.784
They'll tell you that you
need more maintenance

00:04:12.784 --> 00:04:13.819
than your car actually needs.

00:04:13.819 --> 00:04:16.188
In some cases, some
maintenance procedures

00:04:16.188 --> 00:04:18.357
your car doesn't require at all.

00:04:18.357 --> 00:04:21.294
&gt;&gt; David: So, what about that
list of what Cathy's dealership

00:04:21.294 --> 00:04:22.695
says she needs?

00:04:22.695 --> 00:04:24.964
&gt;&gt; PCV valve, I wouldn't
bother changing it.

00:04:24.964 --> 00:04:26.999
It's a lifetime product now.

00:04:26.999 --> 00:04:29.534 align:start position:0%
The spark plugs in this car,
according to the owner's manual,

00:04:29.534 --> 00:04:32.705
is good for 160,000 kilometers.

00:04:32.705 --> 00:04:34.674
She is nowhere near that.

00:04:34.674 --> 00:04:37.176
Change the automatic
transmission fluid, no.

00:04:37.176 --> 00:04:39.712
&gt;&gt; David: That's a big list and
you just said no to a lot of it.

00:04:39.712 --> 00:04:41.046
&gt;&gt; Yeah, absolutely.

00:04:41.046 --> 00:04:42.281
&gt;&gt; David: So what's going on?

00:04:42.281 --> 00:04:45.317
&gt;&gt; Well what's going on here is
the service advisor is trying to

00:04:45.317 --> 00:04:48.755
sell this woman a lot
more work than she needs.

00:04:48.755 --> 00:04:51.023
&gt;&gt; David: Back in Ottawa,
Craig decides they'll stick to

00:04:51.023 --> 00:04:53.826
what's recommended
in the owner's manual.

00:04:53.826 --> 00:04:57.630
But the dealership pushes
back, telling him the manual

00:04:57.630 --> 00:05:00.733
is describing "normal"
driving conditions.

00:05:00.733 --> 00:05:03.870
Here in Ottawa, we have
"special" driving conditions,

00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:05.671
due to the harsh weather.

00:05:05.671 --> 00:05:08.541
&gt;&gt; The owner's manual
says nothing at all about

00:05:08.541 --> 00:05:12.344
special conditions about Ottawa
or any other particular city

00:05:12.344 --> 00:05:15.347
or geographic area or country,
and doesn't say anything

00:05:15.347 --> 00:05:17.716
about the cold weather.

00:05:17.716 --> 00:05:19.218
it doesn't.

00:05:19.218 --> 00:05:21.587
&gt;&gt; David: But it's too
late for Cathy and Craig.

00:05:21.587 --> 00:05:23.255
Did you do the spark plugs?

00:05:23.255 --> 00:05:25.858
&gt;&gt; I did, eventually,
several months later.

00:05:25.858 --> 00:05:27.593
&gt;&gt; David: How do you
feel about that now?

00:05:27.593 --> 00:05:30.463
&gt;&gt; That i was dumb,
that i got taken in.

00:05:30.463 --> 00:05:32.065
&gt;&gt; David: 'Cause this
says, right here,

00:05:32.065 --> 00:05:34.833
in the thing that's in
your car, 160,000 kilometers.

00:05:34.833 --> 00:05:37.370
&gt;&gt; Yeah, that's another
two or three years of driving.

00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:40.372
In spite of knowing
better, i still did it.

00:05:40.372 --> 00:05:41.641
&gt;&gt; David: Because?

00:05:41.641 --> 00:05:44.076
&gt;&gt; Because they
recommend it and they sort of

00:05:44.076 --> 00:05:46.345
plant that little seed of
doubt, and you think,

00:05:46.345 --> 00:05:49.082
well, maybe they DO know
what they're talking about.

00:05:50.449 --> 00:05:52.951 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: Dealerships
in Canada can make, on average,

00:05:52.951 --> 00:05:57.590
only about $1000 to $2500
on each new car sale.

00:05:57.590 --> 00:06:01.827
So their service centres have
become important money makers.

00:06:01.827 --> 00:06:03.730
[ ♪♪ ]

00:06:05.364 --> 00:06:07.299
&gt;&gt; David: Back on
our undercover test,

00:06:07.299 --> 00:06:09.869
Jessica Celsie checks
in at Parkway Honda.

00:06:19.378 --> 00:06:20.279
&gt;&gt; Okay.

00:06:22.181 --> 00:06:24.816
&gt;&gt; Okay, thank you.

00:06:24.816 --> 00:06:26.719
[ ♪♪ ]

00:06:31.824 --> 00:06:34.760 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: A couple hours later,
Jessica gets a phone call

00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:37.530
from an Assistant Service
Manager at Parkway Honda.

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:42.135
&gt;&gt; Okay.

00:07:02.554 --> 00:07:03.622
&gt;&gt; Wow.

00:07:03.622 --> 00:07:05.158
Is that something
that I can think about?

00:07:06.292 --> 00:07:07.193
&gt;&gt; Okay, thank you.

00:07:08.560 --> 00:07:09.462
&gt;&gt; Bye.

00:07:10.829 --> 00:07:11.964
&gt;&gt; Wow.

00:07:11.964 --> 00:07:13.565 line:64%
&gt;&gt; David: 621 bucks

00:07:13.565 --> 00:07:15.801 line:64%
to replace her rear brakes?

00:07:15.801 --> 00:07:21.908
They also recommend a $112
for a brake fluid flush.

00:07:21.908 --> 00:07:23.976
&gt;&gt; If she changes them now,
she'd be changing them

00:07:23.976 --> 00:07:25.645
a bit early.

00:07:25.645 --> 00:07:27.313
She's got 40% left.

00:07:27.313 --> 00:07:29.682
And that might take
another six months.

00:07:29.682 --> 00:07:32.017
She might get a year out of
it, depending on her driving.

00:07:32.017 --> 00:07:34.120
&gt;&gt; And I didn't notice
anything driving the car.

00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:35.621
&gt;&gt; I didn't either.

00:07:35.621 --> 00:07:36.989
When I had the drums
off, everything looked

00:07:36.989 --> 00:07:40.326
perfectly normal
for that age of break.

00:07:40.326 --> 00:07:42.594
&gt;&gt; David: But there's
something critical the dealer

00:07:42.594 --> 00:07:44.030
is not mentioning.

00:07:45.898 --> 00:07:49.268
The largest recall
in automotive history.

00:07:49.268 --> 00:07:51.903
Metal fragments from the
exploding ammonium nitrate

00:07:51.903 --> 00:07:57.643
capsule inside Takata airbags
have killed at least 14 people.

00:07:57.643 --> 00:08:02.314
Hurt more than 180, including
a metal shard that went through

00:08:02.314 --> 00:08:08.321
this woman's face in 2013, while
she was driving her Honda Civic.

00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:11.056
&gt;&gt; I've taken the VIN off
your car and run it through

00:08:11.056 --> 00:08:12.491
the Honda system.

00:08:12.491 --> 00:08:16.095
Your car has a passenger side
airbag that's made by Takata...

00:08:16.095 --> 00:08:17.496 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt;Wow.
&gt;&gt;: ..that needs to be changed.

00:08:17.496 --> 00:08:18.530
&gt;&gt;Wow!

00:08:18.530 --> 00:08:20.466
So why wouldn't they have
mentioned that to me?

00:08:20.466 --> 00:08:22.301
He basically said he would
be doing everything short of

00:08:22.301 --> 00:08:25.471
a safety on it, which, in my
mind, should include an airbag.

00:08:25.471 --> 00:08:27.339 line:76%
&gt;&gt; That is the
number one safety problem

00:08:27.339 --> 00:08:28.841 line:76%
facing your car right now.
&gt;&gt; Right.

00:08:28.841 --> 00:08:30.242 line:78%
&gt;&gt; It's not rear brakes.

00:08:30.242 --> 00:08:31.577 line:78%
it's the airbag recall.

00:08:31.577 --> 00:08:32.911 line:76%
&gt;&gt; And so, for him
not to mention that,

00:08:32.911 --> 00:08:34.780 line:78%
is unbelievable to me.

00:08:34.780 --> 00:08:36.549
[ ♪♪ ]

00:08:36.549 --> 00:08:38.817
&gt;&gt; David: Jessica heads
back to pick up her car.

00:08:38.817 --> 00:08:42.054
Maybe the tell her
about the recall in person.

00:08:42.054 --> 00:08:44.623
The same Assistant Service
Manager from the phone call

00:08:44.623 --> 00:08:47.993
hands her the results
of their inspection.

00:08:47.993 --> 00:08:51.496 align:start position:0%
But, under any
outstanding recalls, incredibly,

00:08:51.496 --> 00:08:54.300
it's checked "no".

00:08:54.300 --> 00:08:56.602
Jessica gives him
another chance to own up.

00:09:04.843 --> 00:09:06.679
&gt;&gt; In the first three or four
times I asked him if there was

00:09:06.679 --> 00:09:08.948
anything wrong with the
car or if it had any other

00:09:08.948 --> 00:09:11.617
safety concerns other than
the brakes, he said no.

00:09:11.617 --> 00:09:13.486 align:start position:0%
&gt;&gt; David: But then,
without having to look it up...

00:09:17.622 --> 00:09:18.623
&gt;&gt; He finally said at the end,

00:09:18.623 --> 00:09:20.359
"Oh, yeah, I think
there's a recall,"

00:09:20.359 --> 00:09:22.227
and then he made mention that
he didn't have the part

00:09:22.227 --> 00:09:24.162
and he'd have to book
a later date for me.

00:09:24.162 --> 00:09:26.198
That just makes me sick.
because I'm now driving a car

00:09:26.198 --> 00:09:28.534
that's unsafe to both
me and my passengers.

00:09:28.534 --> 00:09:31.437
&gt;&gt; David: We contact this
Assistant Service Manager for

00:09:31.437 --> 00:09:34.006
an explanation,
but get no reply.

00:09:34.006 --> 00:09:37.709 align:start position:0%
Why would a dealership
not tell a customer about this?

00:09:37.709 --> 00:09:40.780
&gt;&gt; The dealership has
this business relationship

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:44.917
that's special, under contract,
with the manufacturing facility.

00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:49.121
In that agreement, they have to
do work at a much-reduced rate.

00:09:49.121 --> 00:09:51.289
&gt;&gt; David: Do you think that
ever influences dealerships

00:09:51.289 --> 00:09:53.225
telling people about recalls?

00:09:53.225 --> 00:09:54.660
&gt;&gt; Absolutely.

00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:57.996
&gt;&gt; David: So did it
influence Parkway Honda?

00:09:57.996 --> 00:10:00.566
For weeks, we've been asking
Parkway Honda to come on camera

00:10:00.566 --> 00:10:04.136 align:start position:0%
to explain why they've been
recommending Jessica get service

00:10:04.136 --> 00:10:06.505
she doesn't need but not
telling her about the service

00:10:06.505 --> 00:10:08.307
that she DOES need.

00:10:08.307 --> 00:10:09.308
Well, they've told us
they're gonna do an

00:10:09.308 --> 00:10:11.310
internal investigation
but they will not

00:10:11.310 --> 00:10:12.711
talk to us on camera.

00:10:12.711 --> 00:10:13.712
That's what they've said.

00:10:13.712 --> 00:10:14.946
Let's go chat with them.

00:10:14.946 --> 00:10:16.849
[ ♪♪ ]

00:10:18.517 --> 00:10:20.519
&gt;&gt; David: Service Manager
Ara Pashayan

00:10:20.519 --> 00:10:22.054
stops me at the door.

00:10:22.054 --> 00:10:23.389
&gt;&gt; You're not allowed
in with a cameras.

00:10:23.389 --> 00:10:24.590
This is private property.

00:10:24.590 --> 00:10:25.925
We'd ask that you leave.

00:10:25.925 --> 00:10:28.026
&gt;&gt; David: Okay, but you have
an answer about why she's

00:10:28.026 --> 00:10:29.895
not being told about the recall?

00:10:29.895 --> 00:10:31.530
&gt;&gt; Please, leave.

00:10:31.530 --> 00:10:33.465
You were not allowed here
but you guys are showing up.

00:10:33.465 --> 00:10:34.800
&gt;&gt; David: But it's still...
it's, you know,

00:10:34.800 --> 00:10:36.935
that's not an answer to the
question about why she is

00:10:36.935 --> 00:10:39.305
not being told about a recall.

00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:40.373
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:10:40.373 --> 00:10:41.607
&gt;&gt; David: It's still
not an answer.

00:10:41.607 --> 00:10:43.541
&gt;&gt; We please ask
that you leave.

00:10:43.541 --> 00:10:44.810
&gt;&gt; David: The up-sell continues.

00:10:49.848 --> 00:10:51.483
&gt;&gt; That's just funny.

00:10:51.483 --> 00:10:53.552
That's, like, totally made-up.

00:10:53.552 --> 00:10:55.854
&gt;&gt; David: This is
your Marketplace.

00:10:55.854 --> 00:10:58.323
[ ♪♪ ]

00:10:58.323 --> 00:10:59.392
&gt;&gt; David: The real deal

00:10:59.392 --> 00:11:00.892
on dealerships.

